I had such an incredible time at my high school retreat. We spent several days on Hawaiʻi island at ‘iole @inkohala . Haumana (students) from different mokupuni (islands) came together to malama and 'ike 'äina (take care & learn), we practiced makahiki games, played ukulele, and hana no'eau (art). 
I built new pilina (relationships/friendships) with the most amazing people. 
I love surfing and it’s so special to me but it always feels good to connect with not just the sea but the land, to give back to the land that has given so much to me, to meet and engage with people outside of that circle and open my mind to all the different people/things this beautiful 🌎 has to offer. 
Feeling grounded and right where I’m meant to be ❤️

I was 18 months old in this video and my dad was returning from a year deployment to Iraq. 
Fast forward to today and my dad returned last night from 3 weeks away. My dad joined the military 22 years ago and it’s been a long road full of war, heartache, scars both visible and invisible, endless nights and distance between his family. But it’s also provided us with so much. When I was 5 my dads job transferred us to Hawaii to work for the POW/MIA agency where my dad traveled to places like Cambodia 🇰🇭 and Vietnam 🇻🇳 where their mission was to recover remains from past wars and bring them back home. Since then his sacrifices have continued…another year apart from us and the list goes on. BUT…My dad has provided me this unbelievable life. It’s led me to my home, has provided opportunities for me to chase and live a dream to ensure I love my job and he has IGNITED a passion for adventure and travel to learn about the different places and people of this world. Thank you dad for all of your sacrifices, I love you forever. Happy Veterans Day. ❤️

EVEN if it's a replica of the the MAGIC 🦄 board I still get that buzzing feeling of getting a 🆕 board, still want to get home 🏠 and sticker it up and still rush 🏃‍♀️, to the beach 🌊 so I can test it out! Mahalo @hicsurf ohana, uncle @ktokorosurfboards and auntie @abyukiko for making me feel butterflies 🦋 and making sure my equipment is right and ready for my next adventure 🇧🇷! Thank you for EVERYTHING you do 🤙

Happy 40th birthday to my ride or die! 
My mom is the most selfless person I know. For my entire life she has lead by example and not just preached it to me. She’s been married to my dad for 19 years, worked hard for her career, shown/taught me the importance of honesty and responsibility. But most of all my mom’s always up for adventuring from surf trips in remote places to ski trips to letting me talk her into camping in the back of the truck in board bags in the freezing cold she is always down! 
And she let me have an iPad at age 10 to record some epicness like this…that’s a 🐐 😂
Love you always and forever mom. 
Happy Birthday 🎂
